author: app.com
title: Red Bank Regional football upsets Red Bank Catholic
text:
MORE LITTLE SILVER - Jack Navitsky admits he can not even describe what went through his mind when he saw green grass in front of him when he broke a quarterback isolation play to his left in the fourth quarter Friday night against Red Bank Catholic.
“It was so surreal I don’t even know what to say," said Navitsky, a senior quarterback at Red Bank Regional.
Navitsky began running toward the Red Bank Catholic end zone. He got a key block around the 10-yard line from teammate Chris Outterbridge and completed a remarkable 57-yard touchdown run on a first-and-27 play to give Red Bank its first lead of the night with 6:04 left.
The Bucs’ defense then stopped Red Bank Catholic inches short of a first down on the Red Bank 20 with 1:57 remaining and then ran out the remaining time to record a 24-21 win before an overflowed crowd.
The win, Red Bank’s first over Red Bank Catholic since 2004, enabled it to improve to 6-0 and continue the magical start to its season.
